choices.text:
a woman’s right and a service offered by the Belgian law

Discussion and discussion of abortions are immune to criminal penalties. However, where abortion violates religious beliefs, it is not legal. However, abortion is more common in Catholicism than in the Jewish belief. Besides, abortions are also legal because the religious values taught to the public are determined by paying particular attention to them and not disrespect them. Using the stereotypes to promote abortion rights has one disheartening aspect that is non-response.

Not all girls in the social and governmental environment are in the same position as others to get informed about abortion. In fact, the majority of the women searching for information about abortion are in a crisis and in a position of powerlessness. Therefore, contraceptives may be, difficult to access or even hard for them to use the right one or the right method. Abortion rate in Belgium is quite high in Europe. Women around the world must be aware of the process they have to bear during labor and should never get pregnancies to prevent these problems.

Not only in Belgium but also in other countries such as Ethiopia, most women who are teenagers can’t get proper information about sex or contraception. Deciding the future of unborn depends on these girls using other practices to prevent pregnancy. In the case that a girl became pregnant even though she was using contraceptives, they had to face complications and follow-up treatment.
